Ground-Control-Station for multiple Protocols

* based on OpenGL / OpenGL-ES
* Support for MavLink (Autoquad6, MegapiratesNG, APM2, ...)
* Support for MultiWii-2.1 (MultiWii ...)
* Support for Baseflight (Naze32, MW32 ...)
* Support for UAV-Talk (OpenPilot, CC, C3D, ...)
* Support for NMEA-GPS (über beliebige Serielle Funk-Brücken)
* Support for FrSky-Telemetrie (inkl GPS & RSSI)
* Touchscreens-Optimization
* for Linux-PC's und den Raspberry-PI
* GPL v3


Homepage: http://www.multixmedia.org/Multi-GCS/index.html


Installation:

	Linux/Desktop (OpenGL):

		make -f Makefile.gl-sdl all install

	Linux/Desktop (OpenGL-ES):

		make -f Makefile.gles-x11 all install

	Linux/Raspberry-Pi:

		make all install



Raspberry-PI:
#cat /boot/config.txt 
hdmi_safe=1
hdmi_drive=2
disable_overscan=1
overscan_left=0
overscan_right=0
overscan_top=0
overscan_bottom=0
hdmi_group=2
hdmi_mode=22
arm_freq=700
core_freq=250
sdram_freq=400
over_voltage=0

#cat /root/.multigcs/setup.cfg 
model_name		
view_mode		7
contrast		0
screen_w		1280
screen_h		720
screen_border_x		32
screen_border_y		28
keep_ratio		1.422200

#cat /etc/rc.local
#!/bin/sh -e

/etc/init.d/dbus restart
/etc/init.d/bluetooth restart
su - root -c gcs

exit 0


